<item>
            <title>[HIVE-27865] HMS in http mode shuts down silently with no errors</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-27865</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;After the &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-27340&quot; title=&quot;ThreadPool in HS2 over HTTP should respect the customized ThreadFactory&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HIVE-27340&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HIVE-27340&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, threads in the jetty pool are all daemon threads, such thread pool does not prevent the JVM from exiting when HMS finishes the main thread:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;metastore-0 metastore 1 96e7e920-067b-4134-9abe-c731d12bc8eb [mdc@18060 class=&quot;metastore.HiveMetaStore&quot; level=&quot;INFO&quot; thread=&quot;main&quot;] Started HTTPServer for HMS 
metastore-0 metastore 1 96e7e920-067b-4134-9abe-c731d12bc8eb [mdc@18060 class=&quot;hook.AtlasHook&quot; level=&quot;INFO&quot; thread=&quot;shutdown-hook-0&quot;] ==&amp;gt; Shutdown of Atlas Hook&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We should provide a way to avoid the silent shutdown as what we do in HiveServer2 http mode:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/hive/blob/master/service/src/java/org/apache/hive/service/cli/thrift/ThriftHttpCLIService.java#L282&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/hive/blob/master/service/src/java/org/apache/hive/service/cli/thrift/ThriftHttpCLIService.java#L282&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
